<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-24T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-24T18:00:00-05:00" n="805" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d805">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/651: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul General at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-24T19:00:00-04:00">May
                                        24, 1940—7 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your 30, May 20, 4 p.m. Department deems it important that all
                                American citizens alike receive the invitation to return to the
                                United States while there still remains opportunity for them to do
                                so. Department has noted your despatch No. 1003, July 12, 1939,<note n="58" xml:id="d805fn58">Not printed.</note> suggesting channels
                                through which such invitation may be made.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>